               <head>Persian letter addressed to BEIC Court of Directors</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009117611 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115489" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4235-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Large letter or murāsilah lacking seal or invocation addressed to the <q>kursī nishīn va sāyir-i aʿāẓim-i buzurgān-i kampanī</q> or the <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n87912620" type="org">Chairman, and Elders (or Directors) of the Company</name>,
mentioning <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_44733962" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n93023258" role="subject">Gore Ouseley</persName> as ambassador 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated </p>
                        <p>Clear shikastah āmīz </p>
                        <p>Irregularly cropped, stained, old fold lines</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 23 Nov 1926
</p>
                        <p>Reverse with seal of Prime Minister Muḥammad Shafīʿ 1218 </p>
                        <p>Inscribed on reverse: 1) <q>From one of the Persians of the Persian Court to the Chairman &amp; Court of Directors - on the arrival of Sir Gore Ousley (sic) as Ambassador proposing to open a Correspondence</q>; 2) <q>Received from the Exam. Off. 30 Aug. 1815</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Watermark: 1) Cyrillic inscription; 2) dated 1801; 3) profile figure holding lance with rampant quadruped with scimitar in fenced encloser </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="eng">Persian &amp; English</textLang>
